I have deployed kind cluster.

helm install consul hashicorp/consul --values=values.yaml --debug

export CONSUL_HTTP_ADDR=https://127.0.0.1:8501
export CONSUL_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY=false
kubectl get secret consul-bootstrap-acl-token -o yaml
echo XXXXXXXXXXX | base64 -d
export CONSUL_HTTP_TOKEN=019309ecXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX0b3dcd6
kubectl port-forward svc/consul-server 8501:8501    (on other terminal)

To register external service static-server, run below command:-
curl -k --request PUT --data @external-service.json --header "X-Consul-Token: 019309ecXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX0b3dcd6" https://localhost:8501/v1/catalog/register

To validate connectivity from static-client to external service static-server :-
kubectl debug -it static-client-74bc477bcd-6prr9 --image=nicolaka/netshoot -- sh

~ # curl static-server
"hello world from static-server external service"

Proof: That static-client app talking to static-server through terminating gateway
kubectl debug -it static-client-74bc477bcd-6prr9 --image=nicolaka/netshoot -- sh
curl localhost:19000/clusters
You'll see below output:
